docs.abstract: Sheriff’s Deputy Aaron Russell, 23, is accused of fatally shooting an unarmed man, Nicholas Bils, 36, in the back.
docs.snippet: Sheriff’s Deputy Aaron Russell, 23, is accused of fatally shooting an unarmed man, Nicholas Bils, 36, in the back.
docs.lead_paragraph: The San Diego County District Attorney’s Office on Monday charged a sheriff’s deputy with second-degree murder in the killing of an unarmed man in May — a rare instance of criminal charges being brought against an officer for actions on the job.

docs.abstract: Eight short plays take cues from the 1930 Noël Coward comedy — but now the stakes are different.
docs.snippet: Eight short plays take cues from the 1930 Noël Coward comedy — but now the stakes are different.
docs.lead_paragraph: An unlikely hodgepodge of names gets dropped in the course of Red Bull Theater’s Short New Play Festival: Virginia Woolf, Rachel Dolezal, Troilus, Cressida, Cervantes, Trump. But the name that gets dropped hardest — dropped in the sense that it all but disappears — is that of the production’s touchstone, Noël Coward.

headline.main: Review: Reliving ‘Private Lives,’ This Time Mostly Women’s
headline.print_headline: Short Plays That Take Their Cue From Coward

docs.abstract: This quietly brilliant coming-of-age series from 2019 has new resonance with its arrival to streaming in 2020.
docs.snippet: This quietly brilliant coming-of-age series from 2019 has new resonance with its arrival to streaming in 2020.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the pilot of “David Makes Man,” Dr. Woods-Trap (Phylicia Rashad) is speaking to her gifted middle school class about history and family origins. She talks about the complexities and unanswered questions of the past, then turns the focus to her students: “What is your story? Will there be one?”

headline.main: ‘David Makes Man’ and the Matters of a Young Black Life
headline.print_headline: Learning How to Be  His Own Black Man

docs.abstract: Images of his beating at Selma shocked the nation and led to swift passage of the 1965 Voting Rights Act. He was later called the conscience of the Congress.
docs.snippet: Images of his beating at Selma shocked the nation and led to swift passage of the 1965 Voting Rights Act. He was later called the conscience of the Congress.
docs.lead_paragraph: Representative John Lewis, a son of sharecroppers and an apostle of nonviolence who was bloodied at Selma and across the Jim Crow South in the historic struggle for racial equality, and who then carried a mantle of moral authority into Congress, died on Friday. He was 80.

headline.main: John Lewis, Towering Figure of Civil Rights Era, Dies at 80
headline.print_headline: John Lewis, Civil Rights Icon and Congressman, Dies at 80

docs.abstract: Largely outside of the limelight, athletes like Maya Moore, who helped win the freedom of Jonathan Irons in a questionable conviction, have led the charge for social change.
docs.snippet: Largely outside of the limelight, athletes like Maya Moore, who helped win the freedom of Jonathan Irons in a questionable conviction, have led the charge for social change.
docs.lead_paragraph: Still in her prime, Maya Moore sacrificed her career, stepping away as one of the greats in basketball for a long shot bid to help free a prisoner she was convinced had been wrongfully convicted.

headline.main: W.N.B.A. Star’s Role in Freeing Man From Prison Shows Female Athletes at Forefront
headline.print_headline: As Athletes Pursue Justice, Women Are a Force Without Fanfare
